Ready to build your career? We want to hear from you.
As a Legal Counsel within Pomerleau’s Operational Support team, you will play a key role in the company’s future success by providing strategic legal advice in business law and commercial law. Supporting large-scale construction projects—ranging from $1.5 million to over $1 billion—you will act as a subject‑matter expert to support the daily activities and operations of the company (Pomerleau and its subsidiaries).
What you will do
•	Prepare, review, analyze, comment on, and negotiate various types of contracts (including, among others, different types of construction contracts, subcontracts, service agreements, etc.);
•	Advise project team members on any legal-related matters;
•	Maintain and update the company’s and its subsidiaries’ template library and certain corporate documents;
•	Review, analyze, and comment on documentation for public tender processes, including for alternative delivery projects;
•	Respond to legal inquiries and support company personnel involved in operations across various projects;
•	Coordinate and collaborate with external legal counsel;
•	Perform any other related tasks connected to the operations of the company and its subsidiaries.
This role could be for you if you have
•	A bachelor’s degree in law and membership with the Québec Bar (membership in another Canadian provincial bar will be considered an asset);
•	Approximately five years of experience in commercial and corporate law;
•	Relevant experience with PPP type contractual agreements (considered a significant asset);
•	Practical knowledge of the construction industry;
•	Excellent negotiation and persuasion skills;
•	Strong legal argumentation abilities, both written and verbal;
•	Good knowledge of computer tools and job related software;
•	Ability to demonstrate judgment, initiative, leadership, autonomy, versatility, and team spirit;
•	An analytical and solutions oriented mindset;
•	Strong ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines;
•	Capacity to manage multiple files simultaneously;
•	Willingness to travel occasionally to different regions of Canada where work related representation may be required.
Benefits
•	RRSP with up to 5% employer matching
•	Hybrid work model for corporate roles
•	Employee stock ownership program
•	Career growth through real development opportunities
•	Transit pass reimbursement — get to work for free
•	Minimum 4 weeks of vacation from day one
For the past four years, we've proudly held the distinction of being one of Canada's Top 100 Employers.
